Key Match Events: India won by 10 wickets with 28 balls remaining.
Tushar Deshpande claimed his first international wicket by dismissing Sikandar Raza.
Miscellaneous Highlights: India achieved an unassailable 3-1 lead in the series.
Zimbabwe's innings included a solid opening partnership of 63 runs in 8.4 overs.
Jaiswal and Gill hit 10 fours in the first four overs of India's innings.
Zimbabwe's total of 152/7 was competitive but not match-winning.
